The paper deals with distributed computation and communication costs, which are central topics in the Distributed Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The use of statistical and graph problems suggests that the paper may also belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The investigation of approximation and data distribution suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the focus on communication costs and optimization suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
